data.name: Run commands with different Node.js versions

data.text: Sometimes it can be useful to have a local version of a package as a dependency. You can use `npm link` to link one local package into another. Run `npm link` in the package you want to use. This creates a global reference. Then go into your original package and run `npm link <package-name>` to link in the other package.
You can now use `rainbow` as a dependency in the `unicorn` package.
